#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code nearest smaller element on left nikalne ke liye monotonic increasing stack use karta hai.

1. Stack me indices store hote hain.
2. Pehle element ke left me kuch nahi hota, isliye uska answer -1 hota hai.
3. Har index i ke liye stack se tab tak pop karte hain jab tak top wala element
   current element se greater ya equal ho.
4. Iske baad:
   - agar stack empty ho gaya, to left me koi smaller element nahi hai → answer -1
   - warna stack ke top par nearest smaller element ka index hai → uski value answer me add kar do
5. Fir current index ko stack me push kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Stack me sirf useful elements rakhe jaate hain.
Jo elements current se bade ya equal hain, wo nearest smaller kabhi nahi banenge,
isliye unhe hata dete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.*;
public class Solution
{
    public static ArrayList<Integer> prevSmaller(ArrayList<Integer> A)
    {
        //You can code here
        int n = A.size();
        ArrayList<Integer> result = new ArrayList<>();
        result.add(-1);
        ArrayDeque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        stack.push(0);

        for(int i=1; i<n; i++){
          while(!stack.isEmpty() && A.get(stack.peek()) >= A.get(i)){
            stack.pop();
          }

          //Now if stack is empty
          if(stack.isEmpty()){
            result.add(-1);
          }
          else{
            result.add(A.get(stack.peek()));
          }
          stack.push(i);
        }
        return result;
    }
}
